        <h2>Information</h2>
        <p style="font-weight: bold">
        Mogra is known as Arabian Jasmine in English. It is also known as Samagupita and Jasminum Sambac.
        It is a vine or small shrub that grows 1.6 to 9.8 ft in height.
        The strongly scented Mogra flowers have white corolla bloom throughout the year. These lovely flowers bloom to burst after sunset and close in the morning, which leads to them being called Moonflowers.
            </p>
